WEBVTT

03:23.437 --> 03:24.906
Why do you have
to go so far from the city

03:24.939 --> 03:26.440
to take care
of some old geezer?

03:26.473 --> 03:28.009
We really need the money.

03:28.042 --> 03:29.409
Did you forget
about the eviction notice?

03:29.443 --> 03:32.680
She's getting way more than what
you make in a month waitressing.

03:32.714 --> 03:35.817
Says Miss No Job.

03:35.850 --> 03:38.351
I'm trying. You know
I'm gonna help out when I can.

03:38.385 --> 03:39.721
Mm-hm. Sure.

03:39.754 --> 03:41.989
So, how does a waitress
get a car like this, Maria?

03:42.023 --> 03:43.991
- Mm-hm.
- James Miller.

03:44.025 --> 03:46.561
Ew. I thought
you didn't like him.

03:46.594 --> 03:48.261
Well, I like his car.

03:48.295 --> 03:51.566
- You stole it?
- No, I... I borrowed it.

03:51.599 --> 03:53.968
- So, what do you...
- It's nice to keep.

03:56.303 --> 03:57.605
Is that him?

03:57.638 --> 04:00.340
- I think so.
- I told you we were running late.

04:00.373 --> 04:01.743
- No sweater.
- Let's get out.

04:01.776 --> 04:03.243
Come on,
come on, come on.

04:05.445 --> 04:07.548
Thanks.

04:07.582 --> 04:10.685
- Miss Cherry Holly?
- Yes, nice to meet you.

04:10.718 --> 04:12.587
I'm Dwayne from the Hallawells.

04:12.620 --> 04:13.688
Thank you for picking me up.

04:14.956 --> 04:16.924
- Here.
- Thank you.

04:17.959 --> 04:19.292
Here you go.

04:19.326 --> 04:21.028
Thanks. I can take it myself.

04:21.829 --> 04:22.997
Okay. Thank you.

04:24.364 --> 04:26.067
We love you.

04:26.100 --> 04:27.235
We'll see you next week,
sis, okay?

04:27.267 --> 04:29.070
- Call us when you get there, please, okay?
- Seriously.

04:29.103 --> 04:30.671
Of course, of course.

04:32.640 --> 04:35.375
Love you. Okay,
drive safe, please.

04:35.408 --> 04:37.945
- I'll try.
- And get that car back to that man.

04:37.979 --> 04:40.782
Oh, can I sit up front?

04:40.815 --> 04:42.550
- As you wish, miss.
- Okay, thank you.

04:44.351 --> 04:45.452
Thanks.

05:20.453 --> 05:22.455
Can we stop for something
cold to drink?

05:23.724 --> 05:25.593
My treat.

05:25.626 --> 05:28.062
Sorry, there's nothing
along the road.

05:34.802 --> 05:35.870
You like it?

05:37.872 --> 05:38.940
It was my grandma's.

05:54.622 --> 05:55.857
We're here.

06:20.480 --> 06:21.716
Wait here a moment.

06:31.458 --> 06:33.628
Miss Hallawell is ready
to see you now.

06:35.062 --> 06:37.131
No, please.
I'll take care of it.

07:02.623 --> 07:03.791
Please sit.

07:09.530 --> 07:11.632
It's so nice to meet you,
Miss Hallawell.

07:22.610 --> 07:23.744
Thank you.

07:36.190 --> 07:38.693
I truly appreciate this
opportunity, Miss Hallawell.

07:39.860 --> 07:41.195
I really need this job.

07:42.997 --> 07:44.665
Only 21, correct?

07:45.833 --> 07:47.034
Excuse me?

07:47.868 --> 07:49.203
My age?

07:49.236 --> 07:53.107
- Yes, people sometimes...
- Apart from the hospital,

07:53.140 --> 07:56.077
do you have any other experience
caring for the elderly?

07:57.211 --> 07:58.478
No.

08:00.881 --> 08:03.551
I expect you to take
excellent care of my father.

08:04.952 --> 08:06.087
You can count on me.

08:15.730 --> 08:17.798
Due to a skin condition,

08:17.832 --> 08:20.601
my father cannot be exposed
to strong light.

08:21.836 --> 08:24.271
Only use the gas lamps.

08:24.305 --> 08:28.209
The drapes must remain closed
even during the night.

08:35.016 --> 08:36.250
Wait.

09:01.342 --> 09:02.710
Come.

09:25.800 --> 09:28.035
Father.

09:31.772 --> 09:33.774
This nurse

09:34.942 --> 09:37.678
will be caring for you
while I'm away.

10:14.415 --> 10:17.251
Dwayne goes into town
every Thursday.

10:17.284 --> 10:21.622
To get father's blood supply
from donors at the hospital.

10:24.058 --> 10:26.794
How can I reach you
if there's an emergency?

10:26.827 --> 10:30.698
Dwayne will go into town,
and communicate with me.

10:32.733 --> 10:34.768
There are no telephones
in this house.

10:48.048 --> 10:49.083
Dwayne!

10:51.318 --> 10:52.953
She will eat in the kitchen.

10:56.957 --> 10:59.026
I'm sorry. I...

11:00.261 --> 11:01.295
Sorry.

11:19.346 --> 11:20.814
It's really good.

11:25.819 --> 11:27.054
Thank you.

14:02.076 --> 14:03.645
While I am away,

14:03.678 --> 14:05.913
the house
is your responsibility.

14:14.955 --> 14:16.457
And the girl, too.

14:34.509 --> 14:36.210
Good morning, Mr. Hallawell.

15:23.558 --> 15:24.692
Dwayne.

15:26.460 --> 15:28.563
- Miss?
- Call me Cherry.

15:31.098 --> 15:32.534
Can you lower the heater?

15:34.569 --> 15:36.170
We don't have a heater.

15:47.247 --> 15:48.550
Whose piano is that?

15:51.452 --> 15:53.420
It's Mr. Phillip's.
He used to play.

15:57.124 --> 15:59.159
Why? Do you play?

16:00.027 --> 16:01.596
No. I dance.

20:12.345 --> 20:13.781
Cherry.

20:15.817 --> 20:17.384
You shouldn't touch that.

20:21.288 --> 20:23.758
Oops.

20:23.791 --> 20:25.960
I'm going into town.
Do you need anything?

20:27.762 --> 20:29.229
Yes, please.

20:34.769 --> 20:35.837
Love letter?

20:37.004 --> 20:38.305
Maybe.

20:40.675 --> 20:41.876
It's to my friends.

20:46.614 --> 20:47.815
Okay, I'll see you later.

20:48.883 --> 20:50.250
See ya.

21:24.752 --> 21:25.853
Sorry.

21:53.881 --> 21:55.817
Dwayne told me
you used to play the piano.

21:59.452 --> 22:01.522
I would love to learn
how to play an instrument.

22:03.791 --> 22:05.092
I'm a great dancer, though.

22:05.927 --> 22:07.360
At least I think I am.

25:25.593 --> 25:27.028
Cherry.

25:27.061 --> 25:28.262
Cherry, wake up.

25:29.296 --> 25:30.631
Cherry.

25:47.048 --> 25:48.249
Come on.

25:56.190 --> 25:57.591
Are you okay?

25:58.225 --> 25:59.560
I'm okay.

26:06.200 --> 26:07.635
You're a good caregiver.

26:10.037 --> 26:11.305
Almost as good as me.

26:14.642 --> 26:16.310
You must have had
a very caring mother.

26:20.414 --> 26:21.916
Tell me about your family.

26:24.051 --> 26:25.953
We were on a boat

26:25.986 --> 26:27.655
escaping from our island.

26:29.156 --> 26:30.357
There was a storm.

26:32.760 --> 26:34.929
